fix: replace all gradient hero banners with unified dashboard-hero style

The root problem was finally identified and correctly fixed:

Every section (Transactions, Budgets, Net Worth, Loans, Goals, Reports)
was using raw gradient divs with hardcoded white text:
  background: 'linear-gradient(135deg, #16A34A 0%, #0070F3 55%...)'
  color: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.55)'  <-- invisible on light backgrounds

The dashboard uses .dashboard-hero CSS class which resolves to
hsl(var(--surface-elevated)) -- a dark card in dark mode, a light
card in light mode, with text always on var(--text-primary).

This commit replaces ALL hero banners across all 6 sections with the
exact same .dashboard-hero + .hero-stat-card pattern used by the
dashboard. Every section now looks and behaves identically to the
dashboard hero area:

- Transactions: Net Balance + Income/Expense/Count stat cards
- Budgets:      Total Budgeted + Budgets/OnTrack/OverBudget cards
- Net Worth:    Net Worth + Assets/Liabilities/DebtRatio cards
- Loans:        Total Debt + Loans/MonthlyPmts/Overdue cards
- Goals:        Total Saved + Goals/Achieved/AlmostThere cards
- Reports:      Net Savings + Income/Expenses/SavingRate cards

All amounts use fmtAdaptive(). All status colors use CSS token vars
(var(--success), var(--danger), var(--warning), var(--text-primary)).
No hardcoded hex colors remain in any hero banner across the entire app.
